radiographic_examinations.findings: Dilated appendix measuring up to 7 mm with surrounding fat stranding in the mesentery and thickening of the base of the cecum. No fluid collection or abscess adjacent to the appendix. No free air in the mesentery. Visualized small and large bowel are normal. Urinary bladder and reproductive organs are unremarkable. No pelvic lymphadenopathy or free fluid. The infrarenal abdominal aorta and iliac vessels are normal in caliber. No concerning bony lesion is seen.
